originalText.text: Took the plating 101 class, overall positive experience. Instructors were knowledgeable, however did not go into the depth expected of showing different techniques and tools. Was more so a playground to test techniques you may have seen elsewhere. Was expecting a bit more depth / tutorials. With that said because this was a plating class it's more artistic so I imagine their other classes may go into further depth based on reviews I've seen.

originalText.text: Had such a fun night with city cooking !!! I booked the cooking with truffles class we made fresh pasta with yummy truffles !!!! I was hesitant to book alone but my group was so much fun ! Also chef ken was amazing super informative and so funny I loved how easy it was and the best part eating!!!! I recommend this for singles or couples and fun for a girls night! They served wine. I do not drink but I enjoyed the sparking water ! They also served a dessert to end the amazing meal we cooked ! Worth every penny ! I can not wait for the sushi making class !

originalText.text:
After a long hunt for a Knife Skills class that wasn't all the way downtown and on a weeknight, I found City Cooking West End. Four of us signed up together and were part of a class of 10 people on a Saturday afternoon.   Chef Ken was terrific; relaxed, very interactive, and he made the class fun and informative. He also prepared us a delicious meal that included all the different things we'd chopped and cut while learning how to use our knives, and the class sat down and had a lovely, social lunch together. They even bagged up the leftover things we'd cut up to take home, which I used the very next day.  From start to finish, the experience was everything I was hoping for and more.

Steph is lovely and accommodating, and we definitely want to take more classes at City Cooking West End!

originalText.text: Hosted a corporate team building event with City Cooking and it was a blast! From start to finish, the structure of the night was well thought-out and flowed nicely. Even the planning phase leading up to the event was worthy of praise because Stephanie was so understanding and communicated well. The hosts were super personable, which made it not only educational, but extremely fun. We added the cocktail option, and it was worth it!

I thoroughly enjoyed the Knife Skills 101 Cooking Class! It was informative, helpful and fun. The meal that we helped prepare was delicious! Our instructor Lany was delightful!
I enjoyed the class so much, that as soon as I got home, I signed up for another cooking class!
